<br>
Example, (yes Im biased, I've played my zerk since release), Zerks other then a select few RR7+ folks were not getting the omg 1000+ hits until end regen was released.  Most are still not.  Most zerk damage is greater then BM/Merc but less then LW Hero/Polearms.  Frenzy allowed for a greater high end ability.  So they added one thing (end regen) and it seemed to tip the scales from a balance, but instead of evaluating that, they moved on and made many changes to Albion characters (not giving an opinion on the changes just stating) and zerker and SZ population went up. Was this because of End regen? was it a response needed to combat the new Albion changes?  We don't know because not enough testing or thought was done.    <br>
Zerk and SZ population kept going up; so 2 things have changed, alb changes and end regen.  So there answer?  Lets change end regen and left axe damage itself leaving the high end crits alone.  The RvR and PvE balance is a huge multi-variable system.  Each element interacts on every other element.  Its much harder to &quot;fix&quot; something in one direction or another when you change multiple variables as oppossed to changing 1 or 2.<br>
<br>
Suppose they rolled back the left axe changes and kept the end regen change.  If zerk/SZ population contiues upward and/or damage done doesn't change, then come back to left axe changes.  <br>
<br>
My biggest beef is not in the changes themselves, although as a zerk I'm not happy about them, but mythics track record.  They change something and don't come back to it for months.  They don't finish something.  Take one thing, or one group of things and work them till they are finished.<br>
<br>
For Example: Why did Merc/BM population differ so much from Zerk population in percentage of people played in a realm vs. # of classes?  <br>
Thats a valid question for balance.  People will not play a class if its not balanced with others or it lacks a fun factor.  As well as other reasons. <br>
<br>
Along with that question ask, Why is the population of Zerks/SZs going up faster then other classes in Midgard?<br>
<br>
There is a causality to everything within the game. As its a closed system with rules that can be changed to reach a certain point, its a great candidate for looking at it as a whole system as oppossed to individual problems. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=k8tpitta>k8tpitta</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary TL</span><br>  Posts: 394<br> <font color=#000000>(5/22/03 7:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=141.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blargle.com/boardstuff/fuu3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Insult intended?</span><hr size=1> Sorry for picking on you, Avandor, but the comment just got under my skin.<br>
